definition.value: Octaanion of 1D-myo-inositol 1,2,5,6-tetrakisphosphate arising from global deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups. Major species at pH 7.3.
The hexaanion of 1D-myo-inositol 1,2,3-trisphosphate arising from global deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups. Major species at pH 7.3.
The hexaanion of 1D-myo-inositol 1,2,6-trisphosphate arising from global deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups. Major species at pH 7.3.
An inositol phosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the four phosphate OH groups of 1D-myo-inositol 2,3-bisphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An inositol phosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phospho groups of 1D-myo-inositol 1,2-bisphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An inositol phosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phospho groups of 1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

A semicarbazide derivative that is semicarbazide in which the amino group at position 2 is replaced by a [1,3-dimethyl-4-(propan-2-yl)-1H-pyrazolo[3,4-b]pyridin-6-yl]amino group and the amino group adjacent to the carbonyl is replaced by a (2,6-dichloropyridin-4-yl)amino group. It is a potent S1P2 antagonist (IC50 = 17.6 nM).
Any sphingosine-1-phosphate receptor (S1PR) antagonist that acts as an antagonist for the subtype 2 receptors (S1PR2).
A primary aliphatic amine that is hexane substituted by an amino group at position 2.
A dipeptide zwitterion resulting from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of aspartame; major species at pH 7.3.
An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of biocytin; major species at pH 7.3.
Major species at pH 7.3
Major species at pH 7.3

An organic heterotetracyclic compound that is 6,7,10,11-tetrahydro-7,11-methanocycloocta[b]quinoline substituted by chloro, 2-aminoethyl, and amino groups at positions 3, 9, and 12, respectively (the 7R,11R-stereoisomer). It is a butyrylcholinesterase inhibitor (IC50 = 1.2muM).
A D-glucoside compound with the 2-hydroxy substituent either absent or replaced by a different functional group.
A fatty alcohol consisting of a hydroxy function at any position of an unbranched saturated chain of fourteen carbon atoms.
An N-substituted aminocarbonyl group that is carbamoyl group substituted by a methyl group at the N-position. Observed as an arginine modification group in the chitinase inhibitor Argifin.
A pyrrolidinone that is succinimide substituted by an amino group at position 3.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3.

An aminopyrrolidine that is pyrrolidine substituted by (2S)-2-aminopropanoyl, amino, carboxy, and 3-boronopropyl groups at positions 1, 3, 3, and 4 (the 3R,4S-stereoisomer). It is a selective arginase inhibitor being developed by Calithera Biosciences for the treatment of solid tumours.

A sulfonamide resulting from the formal condensation of the amino group of 2-aminobenzothiazole with the sulfo group of 4-[(2-hydroxy-3-methoxybenzyl)amino]benzenesulfonic acid. It is an inhibitor of 12-lipoxygenase, being developed by Veralox Therapeutics for the treatment of heparin-induced thrombocytopenia and thrombosis.

A member of the class of indazoles that is 1H-indazole substituted by [4-(4-methylpiperazin-1-yl)-2-(tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-ylamino)benzoyl]amino and 3,5-difluorobenzyl groups at positions 3 and 5, respectively. It is a potent inhibitor of TRKA, TRKB, TRKC, ROS1, and ALK (IC50 values of 0.1 to 1.7 nM), and used for the treatment of NTRK, ROS1 and ALK gene fusion-positive solid tumours.

A member of the class of quinazolines that is quinazoline substituted by (3,4-dichloro-2-fluorophenyl)amino, [1-(prop-2-enoyl)piperidin-4-yl]oxy, and methoxy groups at positions 4, 6, and 7, respectively. It is a potent and irreversible tyrosine kinase inhibitor targeting EGFR and HER2 with exon 20 insertion mutations.
Any glycoside derived from alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->3)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminide.
An EC 3.5.3.* (non-peptide linear amidine C-N hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of arginase (EC 3.5.3.1).

label.value: EC 3.5.3.* (non-peptide linear amidine C-N hydrolase) inhibitor

definition.value: An EC 3.5.* (hydrolases acting on non-peptide C-N bonds) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any non-peptide linear amidine C-N hydrolase (EC 3.5.3.*).
A primary ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the imine nitrogen and primary amine; Major species at pH 7.3.
